The value of turnover on the AustralianStock Exchange (ASX) soared to a record 17.11 billion dlrs inthe first three months of 1987 from 7.50 billion in thecorresponding months of 1986, the ASX said.    Its statement did not give the previous peak.    First quarter volume also rose sharply, to 9.95 billionshares from 4.31 billion a year earlier, it said.    The record volume reflected increased investment inAustralian companies by local and overseas institutions and thepopularity of gold mining and other resource sector shares, theASX said.    In the nine months ended March 31, turnover value climbedto 38.52 billion dlrs from 20.72 billion a year earlier, theASX said.    Volume in the nine month period rose to 24.07 billionshares against 13.15 billion a year earlier, it added. REUTER&#3;